⚙️ 4. How to Trigger Each Stage (Very Practical)

Jira → Orchestrator

* Jira webhook (status change)
* Hits your API

Orchestrator → Dev Agent

* Queue (Kafka / SQS / Redis)

GitHub → Review Agent

* PR webhook

CI/CD → Validation Agent

* GitHub Actions webhook OR
* Call API after deploy step

⸻

🔑 5. Key Design Decisions (DO NOT MISS)

1. State Management

You must track:

* Task status
* PR status
* Agent iteration count

👉 Use:

* DB (Postgres)
* or workflow engine (Temporal)

⸻

2. Idempotency

Webhook can fire multiple times

👉 Always check:

if already processed → ignore

⸻

3. Loop Control (VERY IMPORTANT)

Without this → infinite loops

Add:

* max retries (3–5)
* confidence score
* manual override

⸻

4. Parallel Execution

You said:

multiple tasks in progress simultaneously

Yes — but control it:

👉 Use:

* worker pool
* queue-based execution

⸻

5. Observability

Track:

* which agent did what
* how many iterations
* failures

⸻

